<caaml:SnowProfile xmlns:caaml="http://caaml.org/Schemas/SnowProfileIACS/v6.0.3" xmlns:gml="http://www.opengis.net/gml" xmlns:slf="http://www.slf.ch/snowprofile/1.0" gml:id="3c358b45-63f7-40e2-9625-467b103e11bb"><caaml:metaData><caaml:customData><slf:profiletext-list><slf:profiletext key="TEXT_BLOCK_DEFAULT"><slf:text>PROFILE LOCATION
----------------
PST experiment for team LBI with high-speed camera. On the roof of the last bunker. Snow depth representative for this elevation. The layer of surface hoar is an oddity due to the close proximity of the creek. However, we have also found smaller surface hoar throughout the Davos valley bottom in other shaded areas

PROFILE
-------
About 30 cm of new snow since yeasterday. The snow below is settling. The slab above the surface hoar is still very soft. The layer below the thick crust was very variable (hardness 1 to 3) and consisted of many ice chunks mixed with facets.

RUTSCHBLOCK
-----------
No rutschblock. 
PST: full propagation on the SH

SNOW SURFACE
------------
about 80 cm foot penetration

SNOW DRIFT
----------
as soon as the wind picks up, snow is blown around

ALARM SIGNS
-----------
nothing at this elevation. We tried to walk on flat areas around the creek, but no whumpfing yet. Foot penetration to below the crust.

AVALANCHES
----------
no observations possible</slf:text></slf:profiletext></slf:profiletext-list></caaml:customData></caaml:metaData><caaml:timeRef><caaml:recordTime><caaml:TimeInstant><caaml:timePosition>2019-01-09T13:50:00+01:00</caaml:timePosition></caaml:TimeInstant></caaml:recordTime><caaml:dateTimeReport>2019-01-11T12:39:58+01:00</caaml:dateTimeReport><caaml:dateTimeLastEdit>2019-01-14T09:31:58+01:00</caaml:dateTimeLastEdit></caaml:timeRef><caaml:srcRef/><caaml:locRef><caaml:name>Davos - Fluelabach - SLF windtunnel</caaml:name><caaml:validElevation><caaml:ElevationPosition uom="m"><caaml:position>1640</caaml:position></caaml:ElevationPosition></caaml:validElevation><caaml:validSlopeAngle><caaml:SlopeAnglePosition uom="deg"><caaml:position>0</caaml:position></caaml:SlopeAnglePosition></caaml:validSlopeAngle><caaml:pointLocation><gml:Point id="pointID" srsName="urn:ogc:def:crs:OGC:1.3:CRS84" srsDimension="2"><gml:pos>9.869968 46.807735</gml:pos></gml:Point></caaml:pointLocation></caaml:locRef><caaml:snowProfileResultsOf><caaml:SnowProfileMeasurements dir="top down"><caaml:profileDepth uom="cm">89.0</caaml:profileDepth><caaml:weatherCond><caaml:airTempPres uom="degC">-5.9</caaml:airTempPres></caaml:weatherCond><caaml:snowPackCond><caaml:hS><caaml:Components><caaml:height uom="cm">89.0</caaml:height></caaml:Components></caaml:hS></caaml:snowPackCond><caaml:stratProfile><caaml:Layer><caaml:depthTop uom="cm">0.0</caaml:depthTop><caaml:thickness uom="cm">9.0</caaml:thickness><caaml:wetness uom="">D</caaml:wetness><caaml:grainFormPrimary>PP</caaml:grainFormPrimary><caaml:grainSize uom="mm"><caaml:Components><caaml:avg>0.5</caaml:avg><caaml:avgMax>1.0</caaml:avgMax></caaml:Components></caaml:grainSize><caaml:hardness uom="">F</caaml:hardness></caaml:Layer><caaml:Layer><caaml:depthTop uom="cm">9.0</caaml:depthTop><caaml:thickness uom="cm">10.0</caaml:thickness><caaml:wetness uom="">D</caaml:wetness><caaml:grainFormPrimary>PP</caaml:grainFormPrimary><caaml:grainFormSecondary>DF</caaml:grainF